Over the course of 102 games, a 15-run Rays advantage is nothing. However the Rays runs are often more important because of their starting pitching that keeps them in games and maintains one-run leads before handing the game over to a very competent bullpen. The perception is that the Rays are much better at executing and score a lot more runs. The Jays have struck out only three more times than the Rays. Which team would I rather have playing for me right now? The Rays. Is the Jays season done and over?
